parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel strip sensor can cause the fuel level indicator on the dash to become unreliable, leading to unsafe riding conditions when the engine suddenly dies unexpectedly from lack of fuel.
symptoms: The fuel level reads full permanently even though fuel has been completely depleted
no warning lamps
messages
or other symptoms prior to the issue.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Leak from Gas Tank Flange
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Fuel leaks from the gas tank flange can cause a fire hazard, especially when combined with hot engine components.
symptoms: Fuel leaking from the gas tank flange onto the hot engine
fuel puddle on the floor while the motorcycle is idling
fuel gushing out of the fuel pump area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Pump and Auxiliary Fuel Pump Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump and auxiliary fuel pump can cause fuel leaks, leading to a fire hazard, and engine stalling, which can cause accidents.
symptoms: Fuel leaks from the fuel pump and auxiliary fuel pump
engine stalling
fuel level indicator not working.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause fuel to leak, which can lead to a fire hazard, accidents, or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The motorcycle is leaking fuel without warning
fuel smell is present
fuel pours onto the rider while driving
the fuel tank reads empty when it is full or empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel sensor strip can cause the fuel tank to read empty when it is full or empty, leading to inconvenience and potential safety issues.
symptoms: The fuel tank reads empty when it is full or empty.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Final Drive Unit and Drive Shaft Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the final drive unit and drive shaft can cause the rear wheel to wobble excessively, leading to loss of control and accidents.
symptoms: The rear wheel wobbles excessively
oil is leaking from the final drive unit and drive shaft.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the plastic cam on the throttle body can cause a loss of power and engine control, leading to reduced vehicle performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and potentially increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Sudden loss of power
reduced engine performance
hesitation or stumbling when accelerating
difficulty maintaining speed
engine stalling or hesitation.
